ext":"the property has actually changed. When it is emitted is determined by the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"derived GObject class. If the implementor did not create the property with"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"[explicit_notify](\/\/documentation\/gobject\/explicit_notify, then any call to ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_object_set_property()"},{"text":" results","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"in "},{"code":"notify","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" being emitted, even if the new value is the same as the old."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"If they did pass [explicit_notify](\/\/documentation\/gobject\/explicit_notify, then this signal is emitted only"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"when they explicitly call "},{"code":"g_object_notify()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_object_notify_by_pspec()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"and common practice is to do that only when the value has actually changed."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This signal is typically used to obtain change notification for a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"single property, by specifying the property name as a detail in the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_signal_connect()"},{"type":"text","text":" call, like this:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"(C Language Example):","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"C","code":["g_signal_connect (text_view->buffer, \"notify::paste-target-list\",","                  G_CALLBACK (gtk_text_view_target_list_notify),","                  text_view)"]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"It is important to note that you must use","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"#class@GObject.ParamSpe